100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 23, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, addressing ongoing tensions in Europe as nations grappled with post-war reparations and economic instability. In the United States, the Supreme Court heard a pivotal case regarding the legality of the Federal Reserve's authority, which could significantly impact monetary policy. Meanwhile, in the realm of culture, the Broadway production of "Show Boat" received critical acclaim, marking a new era in American musical theater.
